  "2026-07-23T14:21:38.052Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation start 2026-07-23: selected after live 1,922-item all-status inventory, full canonical metadata/history review, and GitHub/release/security reconciliation. This item is actively edited in one coherent SDK/package authoring wave spanning scaffold contracts, flag arity, install validation, activation freshness, schema storage, renderer ownership, and public documentation; no duplicate item was created."
  "2026-07-23T14:59:19.368Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation evidence: registry dependency names and versions now pass npm-package-arg validation, reject option-leading and shell-control input, and are installed behind npm's explicit -- option fence. The subprocess seam is injected for deterministic POSIX/Windows shell tests; focused security tests passed."
  "2026-07-23T15:30:13.062Z",claude-code-agent,"Verification evidence (2026-07-23): full instrumented repository suite passed 347 files / 6,146 tests with exact 100% statements (41,920/41,920), branches (29,630/29,630), functions (8,532/8,532), and lines (40,744/40,744). pnpm lint passed ESLint, zero jscpd clones, 100% source/export/member docstrings, package-boundary audit, and token-budget gate. pnpm security:scan found no credential-like tracked content; pnpm audit --prod found no known vulnerabilities. Packed artifact proof passed scripts/smoke-npx-from-pack.mjs (version 2026.7.23, 15 packages). A separate fresh /tmp consumer installed the npm tarball, initialized an isolated tracker, generated schema and renderer scaffolds, accepted repeated identical --capability values, rejected conflicting values, installed the scoped renderer, and returned extension doctor ok=true without a global renderer warning."
  "2026-07-23T15:37:20.646Z",claude-code-agent,"Consolidated release-gate evidence: all owned local gates passed, including exact coverage, version policy/sync, secret scan, packed npx smoke, and 88-command package-first dogfood. The aggregate command stopped only at greptile-review because this branch is intentionally not committed yet (reported: no committed code changes to review against main); review convergence will run after push and is not being misclassified as a code/test failure."
  "2026-07-23T15:59:59.677Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #657 CodeRabbit remediation evidence: valid whitespace-bearing comparator ranges are accepted by npm-package-arg. Runtime dependencies are installed from the isolated validated package.json, while the npm shell argv contains only fixed flags and a terminal --; no manifest-controlled spec crosses the Windows shell boundary. Full suite passed 6,146/6,146 at 100/100/100/100 and lint/static/duplication gates passed."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T14:59:20.098Z",claude-code-agent,"Treat caller-controlled package specs as structured npm arguments, not shell text: validate with npm's parser and still fence argv with -- because these controls protect different boundaries."
